print("Welcome to treasure island. Your mission is to find the treasure.\nIn this mission, you will choose which way to go. But beware! Many of the paths will lead to certain death. Continue on, if you dare.")
name = input("Before we begin, what is your name?")
print(f"Hello, "+name+". Which kind of jacket will you be bringing with you, winter, or rain? For winter type W and for rain type R.")
jacket_upper = input(" ")
jacket = jacket_upper.lower()
# Changing the jacket to lower case. We will use this later on.
print("Fantastic. As we set out, the sky is dark and cloudy. Good thing you brought that jacket. We come to our first fork in the road. To the left there are many hills- like in the Hobbit. To your right, there is a great river. Which way do you choose?")
direction_1_upper = input("L, or R?")
direction_1 = direction_1_upper.lower()
score = 0
# I will use their score to keep track of if they have lost- this way I can make a few elif statements without having to nest them all.
if direction_1 == "l":
  print("The mountains are calling, and I must go. John Muir said that. And me. As you approach the foot of the mountains, you notice that a storm is rolling in quickly.")
  direction_2_u = input("Do you want to take shelter in a cave, or keep going? Type cave or continue to indicate your choice.")
  direction_2 = direction_2_u.lower()
  if direction_2 == "cave":
    score += 1
    print("You find a cave just as the storm is hitting, and start making a fire. Soon, you hear a rustling sound. As it turns out, you took the cave of a mother bear and her cubs. She traps you in the cave, and eats you. Womp womp.")
    print('''.'"'.        ___,,,___        .'``.
: (\  `."'"```         ```"'"-'  /) ;
